Unglamorous restaurant that was near the hotel we were staying at. We got there around 10 am on a Thursday so there was no wait. I had the banana fosters french toast. It was very good. Much too much for one person to eat. I would return and try the shrimp and grits.

Absolutely delishious breakfast food here. We came right at 9am on Friday and the place was already getting packed! I ordered the pork belly with cheesy grits while my friends ordered the pulled pork egges benedict and banana butter pecan french toast (which tasted like candy). All of the dishes were excellent and extremely filling. You can't really go wrong with ordering anything here. Just be sure to come early to avoid the 1-2 hour waits!

Holy moly -- the food was incredible!! Highly recommend!! My kids were skeptical & they said that I redeemed myself with this pick! We had the shrimp and grits (wow!! On "Chopped" a contender said that grits can NEVER be made to be yummy -- not true! Brenda's does it to perfection); hush puppies were heavy but good; fried chicken was tasty; biscuits flaked apart and the strawberry / rhubarb spread transported us to the Midwest in 3 clicks! The beignets were light, delectable and melted in the mouth -- recommend the sampler. The long line is worth it and younger / upscale crowd tells you it is THE PLACE TO BE!

Brenda you didn't disappoint... From The beignets... to the granola pancakes... Delicious... and who can beat the prices??!! You need to check it out ASAP.

Oh and the beignets were extremely dense, dry, bland and overall disappointing (see a trend here). We actually considered sending them back since they were so dry but saw the next batch that our neighbors ordered and they looked no better. With so much amazing food in SF, skip this place and the ridiculous waits times.

I don't know many places where you can get French soul food, so extra high ratings for uniqueness. My BFF and I lucked out when we easily found street parking and strolled right in and proceeded to sit down and order. So is it worth the wait? I don't know since I didn't have to wait. But would I come back again? Yes!! You must try the shrimp and grits, crawfish beignets and sweet beignets (get the sampler). Not the healthiest fare but if you have a "cheat day," spend it here.

What an experience. Everything was deliciously awesome. It's just that simple. Here's what we ordered: The Abita Strawberry beer. A house Watermelon iced tea too delicious for words. Friends from school have been telling me to check out Brenda's. I used to volunteer just around the corner, so I was surprised that I've never seen it before. As always, I look at the yelp reviews to see what I should order. We got: -Crawfish Beignets -Red Beans and Rice -Catfish Poboy -Watermelon sweet tea -Okra Gumbo The best thing we ordered has got to be the beignets. The filling was nice and warm and the seasoning was great! I definitely recommend getting this. It is a MUST! I never really had authentic soul food before so I have nothing to compare it to, haha. But I do feel like Brenda's got some nice homecooked-feel items on their menu. I'm giving four stars because I felt a little warm inside. Maybe it's because it was hot that day and the sun was shining right on me haha. Go after 1pm, after the lunch rush. We waited about 5 minutes for a table.

Overrated in my opinion. Long lines for mediocre meal. Maybe I'm just not a fan of cajun food, but I felt like they were dousing every dish with their cajun seasoning such that all you tasted was the seasoning and the flavors of the actual food wasn't able to penetrate through. Brenda's other restaurant, Meat and Three, is a lot better. It's not as in-your-face-cajun as this place and the wait is not as ridiculous

Brenda is serving up some mean soul food here at this local hot-spot in SF. The wait was incredible, seeing as how we had such a large party and a few late comers, but the food was WELL worth the price of admission. Beignets, beignets, beignets!!! EVERYONE at the table was expecting little tasty bites of sweet and savory selections having grabbed 3 flights to taste each morsel. None of us knew we were going to get softball size delectables. Wow! I mean these things were HUGE and we were right to grab each flavor as they were all wonderful. Granted the plain beignet was a bit dull after having all of the other 3 flavors, but still worth it with Brenda's strawberry preserves on the table in front of us. I opted out of the huge meal knowing that I was going to get a taste of everyone's meal. the biscuits are to die for, so I ordered that and their country sausage gravy. Good stuff, but probably not the most flavorful I've experienced... probably why it's not a staple on their menu. The fried green tomatoes were a nice touch the specials of the day. The eggs benedicts were flowing throughout the restaurant with fluffy white eggs and creamy centers surfacing all over the table. Brenda is not shy of her sauce - let me just say that. I believe everyone quickly forgot about the wait and had a pleasant time drinking mimosas and sipping coffee while staring at soon-to-be-empty plates. thanks for doing us right Brenda!

The fold was delicious and very filling. Would highly recommend as one of the top breakfast/brunch locations in all of SF. I left very satisfied with the service as well as the quality of the food.

I came here on Superbowl Sunday for brunch, so there was a short wait and plenty of parking. From what I understand both of these things are unusual. I did have the typical experience though - great food! Most of the food is pretty rich so pace yourself and/or bring friends so you can share. I loved the beignets, particularly the crawfish. The shrimp omelette I had was a bit too much to handle.

    As always, I look at the yelp reviews to see what I should order. We got:
    -Crawfish Beignets
    -Red Beans and Rice
    -Catfish Poboy
    -Watermelon sweet tea
    -Okra Gumbo

    I never really had authentic soul food before so I have nothing to compare it to, haha. But I do feel like Brenda's got some nice homecooked-feel items on their menu.

    I'm giving four stars because I felt a little warm inside. Maybe it's because it was hot that day and the sun was shining right on me haha. Go after 1pm, after the lunch rush. We waited about 5 minutes for a table.
